\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Newsletter strategies for the bootstrapped founder\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 How to launch your first SaaS roundup\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Start small. A SaaS roundup is the perfect way to offer value without overwhelming yourself.\
Think: three to five curated links or updates\'97tools you love, product news, or trends your users should know about.\
Add a short intro with your perspective, keep the tone light, and use a clear format so it\'92s easy to scan.\
Most importantly, send it consistently. Weekly, bi-weekly, or monthly\'97just pick a rhythm you can stick to. Done well, roundups create trust and position you as a helpful expert.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf0 Creating a SaaS weekly newsletter without burning out\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 The secret to sending consistently without frying your brain? Systems.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li800\fi-800\ri800\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \uc0\u55357 \u56481  Create a template once and reuse it. Batch your content ideas in advance. Keep a swipe file of useful links, screenshots, or product updates as they happen. Schedule a fixed time each week to write.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Don\'92t overthink\'97what\'92s helpful is enough. And remember, not every issue has to be groundbreaking. Sometimes a great tip or a smart link is all it takes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Your newsletter doesn\'92t need to be fancy, just valuable\
